
Overview of verb exhibit

The verb exhibit has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (13) exhibit -- (show an attribute, property, knowledge, or skill; "he exhibits a great talent")
2. (11) expose, exhibit, display -- (to show, make visible or apparent; "The Metropolitan Museum is exhibiting Goya's works this month"; "Why don't you show your nice legs and wear shorter skirts?"; "National leaders will have to display the highest skills of statesmanship")
3. (4) show, demo, exhibit, present, demonstrate -- (give an exhibition of to an interested audience; "She shows her dogs frequently"; "We will demo the new software in Washington")
4. parade, exhibit, march -- (walk ostentatiously; "She parades her new husband around town")
